Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.50,0:00:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(800,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.43,0:00:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.70,0:00:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.84,0:00:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.92,0:00:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.93,0:00:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.27,0:00:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.52,0:00:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.65,0:00:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.87,0:01:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.88,0:01:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.97,0:01:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Terrifying Revival Combo"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.14,0:01:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His Deck Master Ability... Reflector Hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.04,0:01:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He redirected my own attack at me,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.84,0:01:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and I reduced my own Life Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.08,0:01:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Italian political philosopher\Nof the Renaissance once said...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.98,0:01:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It is more profitable to utilize your enemies than it is your allies."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.63,0:01:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A universal proverb again?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.76,0:01:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But because of the Special Ability you used just now,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.92,0:02:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you don't have a single Monster on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.73,0:02:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Battle Phase isn't over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.06,0:02:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can use direct attacks, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.03,0:02:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Retrained Elf Swordsman!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.23,0:02:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That one was a little dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.04,0:02:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have more Monsters, this holding the advantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.48,0:02:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you keep any sacrifices you plan to Summon a Monster with!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.28,0:02:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you {\i1}say{\i0} so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.37,0:02:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to the damage I took just now, I can Special Summon a Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.32,0:02:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Ruklamba the Spirit King!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.89,0:02:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.19,0:02:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Monster that you can Summon after receiving damage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.67,0:02:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the player holding Ruklamba the Spirit King receives 1000 points of damage or more,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.85,0:02:48.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can Summon Ruklamba the Spirit King from your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.11,0:02:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better remember that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.54,0:02:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So he uses a Revival Combo that lets him substitute his Monsters whenever they are destroyed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.18,0:02:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We don't have the time to waste on him...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.79,0:03:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're finished, declare "turn end" already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.29,0:03:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realize that you have a strong defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.76,0:03:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't win if you do nothing but defend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.16,0:03:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Defending is an easier and stronger way to fight than attacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, it requires a strong mentality to maintain your status quo and conserve your resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.47,0:03:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some people out there are not capable of such thought process.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.87,0:03:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there is no better strategy out there than simply maintaining your present situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.14,0:03:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will come to understand this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.21,0:03:26.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.84,0:03:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't waste the chance I gave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.51,0:03:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, what's the {\i1}rest{\i0} of the group up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.61,0:03:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.95,0:04:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mom was already dead and Dad died from an accident shortly after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.18,0:04:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our relatives only wanted our Dad's inheritance...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.46,0:04:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And sent me and my brother to this orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.55,0:04:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.72,0:04:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My big brother and me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.04,0:05:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's done! It's done! I built a castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.47,0:05:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure did!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.01,0:05:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right.. I was remembering the happy times we spent with Mom and Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.66,0:05:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba! Mokuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.86,0:05:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.74,0:05:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back, Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.85,0:05:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Big Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.82,0:05:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I could turn back time to when Dad was alive
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.61,0:05:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I went to the park where I used to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.32,0:05:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba, stop crying. I know how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.76,0:05:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't loser dogs or trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.33,0:06:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't even think about those who made things like this for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.30,0:06:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just live happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.42,0:06:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, I'll act as your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll protect you, no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.88,0:06:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.30,0:06:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So stop crying now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.81,0:06:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! Don't let {\i1}anyone{\i0} get too close to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.55,0:06:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're done for if they see your weak side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.22,0:06:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those were the clichéd lines you always said, Big Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.47,0:06:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.10,0:06:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Again{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just as good as always, Big Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.91,0:06:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto, the borderline between reality and dreams is imprecisely marked by the vague memories one holds dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.72,0:06:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, human beings struggle...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.28,0:06:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using those feelings, those memories, as they aim for better places in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.95,0:07:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When in reality, they are equivalent to electronic signals that insouciantly choose to enter your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.26,0:07:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People lack the foresight to not allow themselves to be controlled by such mentality...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.50,0:07:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that is why you are not qualified to be the successor to Kaiba Corporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, a person like me who has long surpassed such foolish notions is far more fit for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.07,0:07:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm going to teach this to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.20,0:07:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And quite {\i1}thoroughly{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.05,0:07:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My brother often played with me just like he is now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.58,0:07:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But... After {\i0}that day{\i1},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.49,0:07:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the smile on my brother's face was gone for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.03,0:07:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes, since that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.99,0:07:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Since {\i0}that man{\i1} came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.06,0:07:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The CEO of Kaiba Corporation, Gozaburo Kaiba, has won the World Chess Championship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.61,0:07:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}President Kaiba has decided to donate the cash prize of 100,000 yen to charity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.88,0:07:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.78,0:07:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On that day, up until this very moment even, my plan was put into motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.59,0:08:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i0}him{\i1}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gozaburo... Kaiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.69,0:08:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is the day I'll keep my promise, Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.59,0:08:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.96,0:08:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man is Gozaburo Kaiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.26,0:08:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the director of Kaiba Corporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.89,0:08:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should become his adopted children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.36,0:08:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adopted children?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.32,0:08:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll adopt us for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.76,0:08:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, I'll {\i1}make{\i0} him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.41,0:09:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.95,0:09:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please adopt me and my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say that one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said, "Please adopt me and my brother."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.50,0:09:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, there has to be conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.00,0:09:22.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it will be that you have to adopt us if I beat you in Chess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.25,0:09:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an interesting kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.77,0:09:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that condition is impossible for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.04,0:09:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't become my adopted son like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.54,0:09:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not be aware that I beat six world champions in the World Chess Championship...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.55,0:09:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no {\i1}way{\i0} you can beat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.55,0:09:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a match, no outcome is set in stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.26,0:09:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have absolutely no {\i1}hope{\i0} of beating me in Chess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.16,0:09:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, knowing this, you still challenge me to Chess anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.70,0:09:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter either way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.67,0:09:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you take the challenge? Or will you refuse it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.87,0:09:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which one is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got got a nice look in your eyes there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.45,0:10:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. I'll accept your challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.51,0:10:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll adopt you if you can beat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.05,0:10:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't hold back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.68,0:10:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't {\i1}want{\i0} you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be borrowing one of your classrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.05,0:10:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes! Go right ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.50,0:10:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, you already had everything planned out, up until this very day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.84,0:10:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.31,0:10:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had done research on every single one of his Chess books
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.14,0:10:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon challenging him, I had already memorized his entire strategy, including some additions of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to admit that you've made quite a bold impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.09,0:10:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me the capacity that surpassed the six world champions in the World Chess Championship.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.76,0:10:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we start?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.47,0:11:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This move...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.34,0:11:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I used the exact same moves he did, putting the game in my favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.94,0:11:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Only I used it as a trap...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.59,0:11:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He fell into my traps, one after the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.77,0:11:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.97,0:11:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That moment... If my big brother hadn't beaten Gozaburo that moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.88,0:11:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...the smile on my brother's face wouldn't have disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.59,0:11:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mokuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the past can still be changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.56,0:12:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you'd go back to being the brother I knew who was always smiling!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.87,0:12:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.94,0:12:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.67,0:12:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's imaginary reality Noah's showing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.21,0:12:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.45,0:12:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.18,0:12:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.99,0:13:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Youi in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.16,0:13:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The player opposite of whoever Summons Youi
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.59,0:13:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is not permitted to draw a card next turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.13,0:13:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my turn isn't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.00,0:13:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card Early Burial from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.04,0:13:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I give up 800 of my Life to allow a Monster Card from my Graveyard to revive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.15,0:13:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He increases the amount of Monsters on his field so easily...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.89,0:13:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's time for me to end this Duel already, or else...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might be thinking that you'd like to beat me quickly and get to your friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but you're {\i1}naïve{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.80,0:13:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am terribly sorry, but the reality is that won't be happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.17,0:13:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This lineup again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.21,0:13:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I attack with a Monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.45,0:14:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he'll sacrifice two Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and activate his Deck Master Ability, Reflector Hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.76,0:14:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I get rid of his Wall Monsters
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.33,0:14:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and successfully attack the player directly...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go! Retrained Elf Swordsman!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.05,0:14:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If the player holding Ruklamba the Spirit King receives 1000 points of damage or more,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.43,0:14:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}you can Summon Ruklamba the Spirit King from your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.68,0:14:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Since he can Special Summon from his hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.88,0:14:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my attacks only {\i0}strengthen{\i1} my opponent's line of Wall Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.22,0:14:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have to make sure I don't attack carelessly...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.92,0:14:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.05,0:14:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you so terrified that you've become frozen with fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.89,0:14:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to experience what your Deck Master can do at least {\i1}once{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.63,0:14:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, Kuriboh probably won't do much to prove itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.44,0:15:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let it bother you.\N I believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.34,0:15:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I shall now declare "turn end"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.12,0:15:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.49,0:15:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.66,0:15:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! We finally got outta there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.09,0:15:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's still the Virtual World.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.23,0:15:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how you think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.19,0:15:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's too strange for a dungeon like this to be inside a mobile fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.67,0:15:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going on and on about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.44,0:15:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Let's go find Shizuka-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.14,0:15:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Shizuka-{\i1}chan{\i0}!\N -Shizuka-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.75,0:15:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone, help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.12,0:15:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuka-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.26,0:15:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sideways! Run sideways!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.29,0:15:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No use She can't hear us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.53,0:15:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain in the ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.93,0:15:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.67,0:16:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honda-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.24,0:16:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuka-{\i1}chan{\i0}! This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.86,0:16:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I didn't break a sweat!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.26,0:16:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much, Otogi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.79,0:16:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It was a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.03,0:16:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was thanks to {\i1}me{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.13,0:16:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.00,0:16:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because of the Special Effect of Youi from before...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.24,0:16:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't draw a card this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.67,0:16:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a greater chance of winning a war if you have higher numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.98,0:16:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such advice can be found in countless numbers of strategical books.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.51,0:16:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, it was said back in Ancient China that, "You can't do harm to a battalion."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.65,0:16:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or as they said in France, "Victory lies in keeping a battalion"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.85,0:16:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These proverbs are spoken even today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.66,0:16:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.93,0:17:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A militarist of Prussia once said...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The quantity of troops is just one of the factors in winning."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.57,0:17:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there are many other incidents in history that teaches us the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're annoying! Be quiet already!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.27,0:17:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I attack with Retrained Elf Swordsman,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.88,0:17:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and he uses his Deck Master Ability again...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.15,0:17:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Elf Swordsman will instead directly attack {\i0}me{\i1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.48,0:17:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it will reduce the number of Monsters he has on the field to use for his Deck Master Ability by doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.99,0:17:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the attack of the Elf Swordsman doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.96,0:17:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}make him use his Deck Master Ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.09,0:17:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can still get rid of his sacrificial Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.13,0:17:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's a risk I'm willing to take to get an advantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.59,0:17:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retrained Elf Swordsman, attack Ipiria!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.07,0:17:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this moment, I activate my Deck Master Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.18,0:17:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So he did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Ipiria and Youi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.92,0:17:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And launch the Reflector Hole!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.45,0:17:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which makes the attack of the opponent invalid
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.85,0:18:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and in return steals the Attack Points from the opponent's Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.89,0:18:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's coming...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.28,0:18:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damaged {\i1}twice{\i0} now, eh?\N So, how's it feel? {\i1}Painful{\i0}, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you are attacked one more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.13,0:18:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the mental shock will render your body unable to move,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.69,0:18:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and even if your Life doesn't hit zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.89,0:18:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you could lose your {\i1}actual{\i0} life in this world first.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.63,0:18:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there shouldn't be any Monsters left for him to sacrifice...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.64,0:18:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.81,0:18:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His Tribute Monsters should have disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.31,0:19:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By sacrificing Ruklamba,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.77,0:19:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can Special Summon two Monsters with a total combined Attack Power of 2000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.99,0:19:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the Attack Power of the Monsters you place on the field
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.12,0:19:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must not total higher than 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.29,0:19:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was able to Summon them with Ruklamba's Ability?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.26,0:19:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. So I Summoned another Ruklamba and Wall of Illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.50,0:19:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wall of Illusion...\NIf I remember that wall's Effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.84,0:19:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It can make the Monster attacking it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.04,0:19:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}go back to hand of the player.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.51,0:19:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you beat them down,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.23,0:19:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a new enemy will always take its place!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.69,0:19:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times you attack him, he always counters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.62,0:19:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a lowly strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.41,0:19:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Duel befitting of a man who has taken on the form of a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.57,0:19:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A Wall Monster that forces your Monsters back to your hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:20:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And Ruklamba, whom when damaged, Special Summons more allies...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.47,0:20:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And adding in the Deck Master Ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.48,0:20:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he holds the Effect to make the player damage himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.95,0:20:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The moment I attack him with Chimera,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.38,0:20:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my Life Points will fall to zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.25,0:20:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And what's more... What's with the damage being done to my body?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.02,0:20:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This Duel is too dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.13,0:20:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we don't save the others as soon as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.06,0:20:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they may be in grave danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.20,0:20:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?\NIs this the first time you feel like you'll lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.83,0:20:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't need to feel ashamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.44,0:20:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A general of Prussia once said...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.24,0:20:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A true master of failure will feel his pending fate to lose long before it happens."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.08,0:20:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.25,0:20:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But your body is mine the moment you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.12,0:20:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you were {\i1}destined{\i0} to lose when you chose Kuriboh as your Deck Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.83,0:20:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You at least look {\i1}somewhat{\i0} threatening when you're angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.37,0:21:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you insult Kuriboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.27,0:21:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.67,0:21:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn, then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.81,0:21:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I can't put it in words!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.65,0:21:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea how {\i1}long{\i0} I've been waiting for this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.35,0:21:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My attack will cause you so much mental damage, you won't be able to take it! You'll fall into despair!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.39,0:21:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll {\i1}finally{\i0} get a body at long last!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.53,0:21:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I haven't given up yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.94,0:21:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(141,133)}"Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.44,0:21:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As Yugi is pushed into a corner by the Deepsea Warrior,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.78,0:21:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am caught by Cyclops
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.71,0:21:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in extreme danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.58,0:21:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible that they want to eat me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.68,0:21:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this all just Virtual Reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to hurry and escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.52,0:21:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi is working hard, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.16,0:21:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't lose either!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.66,0:22:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Yugi, don't you dare lose to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.13,0:22:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.76,0:22:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Counterattacking Rainbow Arch"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.46,0:22:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.08,0:22:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.96,0:22:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.26,0:22:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.89,0:22:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.27,0:22:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.82,0:22:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.41,0:22:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.16,0:22:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.25,0:23:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.14,0:23:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.85,0:23:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.82,0:23:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
